The incidence of the prostatic carcinoma as well as the cases treatable by radical prostatovesiculectomy with curative intention is increasing. The exact pathological examination of the specimens defines the stage of disease and subsequently the prognosis and therapeutic consequences. The compatibility of different scientifical studies is made difficult by the lack of a standard in the pathological examination of the specimens. Our exactly defined rational method helps eliminate these troubles and ameliorate the interdisciplinary dialogue.  
